==============================================================================
	SITE CONFIGURATION
==============================================================================
Edit the following for your site:

<supporttop>/config/RELEASE - Set EPICS_BASE to EPICS base pathname.
<supporttop>/xxx/config/RELEASE - Set SUPPORT to <supporttop> pathname.
<supporttop>/utils/Makefile - Set SUPPORT to <supporttop> pathname.
			    - Add/delete support modules by adding/deleting
			    '#' to the four entries for each support module;
			 
			    include $(SUPPORT)/config/<module>_RELEASE
			    DIRS += $(module)
			    RELEASE_FILES += $(module)/config/RELEASE
			    MASTER_FILES  += $(SUPPORT)/config/<module>_RELEASE

To rebuild synApps;

cd <supporttop>/utils
gnumake clean uninstall;gnumake

	
==============================================================================
	STANDARD SUPPORT MODULES
==============================================================================
The following support modules required limited modifications.


MODULE:		bitBus
VERSION:	R1-4
URL: http://www.aps.anl.gov/asd/people/mrk/epics/modules/bus/bitBus/index.html
BUILD DEPENDENCIES: EPICS_BASE


MODULE:		ipac
VERSION:	2.3
URL: http://www.aps.anl.gov/asd/people/anj/ipac/
BUILD DEPENDENCIES: EPICS_BASE
PROCEDURE:
- After unzipping and untarring ipac-2.3.tar.gz; "mv ipac ipac2-3".

MODULE:		mpf
VERSION:	R1-7
URL: http://www.aps.anl.gov/asd/people/mrk/epics/modules/bus/mpf/
BUILD DEPENDENCIES: EPICS_BASE, IPAC
PROCEDURE:
- After unzipping and untarring mpf1-7.tar, "mv 1-7 mpf1-7".
- Applied fix for "Known Problems" as described in,
URL:http://www.aps.anl.gov/asd/people/mrk/epics/modules/bus/mpf/R1-7/knownProblems.html
Changed the stack size for watchDog from 2000 to 4000.
- cd <supporttop>; chmod u+w mpf1-7/config/RELEASE


MODULE:		mpfGpib
VERSION:	R1-4
URL: http://www.aps.anl.gov/asd/people/mrk/epics/modules/bus/gpib/mpfGpib/index.html
BUILD DEPENDENCIES: EPICS_BASE, MPF
PROCEDURE:
- After unzipping and untarring mpfGpib1-4.tar, "mv 1-4 mpfGpib1-4".
- cd <supporttop>; chmod u+w mpfGpib1-4/config/RELEASE
- Replace the contents of mpfGpib1-4/gpibApp/Makefile.Vx with the following;
------- Makefile.Vx -------
PROD      = GpibHideosLocal.o
PROD     += GpibHideosRemote.o

LIBOBJS   = GpibGsTi9914.o
LIBOBJS  += Gpib.o
LIBOBJS  += gpibSniff.o
LIBOBJS  += gpibServer.o
LIBNAME   = mpfgpibserverLib

INSTALLS  = GpibGsTi9914.o
INSTALLS += Gpib.o
INSTALLS += gpibSniff.o
INSTALLS += gpibServer.o
------- Makefile.Vx -------


MODULE:		mpfSerial
VERSION:	R1-3
URL: http://www.aps.anl.gov/asd/people/mrk/epics/modules/serial/mpfSerial/index.html
BUILD DEPENDENCIES: EPICS_BASE, MPF
PROCEDURE:
- After unzipping and untarring mpfSerial1-3.tar, "mv 1-3 mpfSerial1-3".
- Applied fix for "Known Problems" as described in,
http://www.aps.anl.gov/asd/people/mrk/epics/modules/serial/mpfSerial/R1-3/knownProblems.html
Changed the stack size for watchDog from 2000 to 4000.
- cd <supporttop>; chmod u+w mpfSerial1-3/config/RELEASE
- Replace the contents of mpfSerial1-3/serialApp/Makefile.Vx with the following;
------- Makefile.Vx -------
PROD      = devStringMpf.o

LIBOBJS   = OctalUART.o
LIBOBJS  += SerialPort.o
LIBOBJS  += serialPortSniff.o
LIBOBJS  += serialServer.o
LIBNAME   = mpfserialserverLib

INSTALLS  = OctalUART.o
INSTALLS += SerialPort.o
INSTALLS += serialPortSniff.o
INSTALLS += serialServer.o
------- Makefile.Vx -------

==============================================================================
The following support modules required more extensive modifications.
==============================================================================

MODULE:		motor
VERSION:	4-4
URL: http://www.aps.anl.gov/upd/people/sluiter/epics/modules/mechanism/motor/index.html
BUILD DEPENDENCIES: EPICS_BASE, MPF, MPF_SERIAL, MPF_GPIB
PROCEDURE:
- <top>/config/RELEASE. Uncomment MPF_SERIAL=, MPF=, EPICS_BASE=,
			TEMPLATE_TOP=, MSITOP= and MPF_GPIB=
- <top/config/RULES.Db updated to EPICS base R3.13.5 for 'depends' make target.
- <top>/motorApp/Makefile.  All device support selected.
- <top>/motorExApp/Makefile.  Build all motor examples.


